address: 38 Everland-ro 562Beon-gil, Pogog-eup, Cheoin-gu, Yongin-si, Gyeonggi-do, South Korea
description: The Hoam Art Museum is located in Yongin Everland, a place where you can see wonderful works of art. The art exhibitions here are mainly held in the main building of the Hanok style. From the relics of the prehistoric era to the modern art works, there are dazzling and all-inclusive, including more than 100 exhibits including national treasures, which are designated as cultural properties. Visitors can view Buddhist art works, texts and pictures, ceramics and other exhibits here.
